      • pop

        public void pop(AbstractDrawer drawer,
       org.apache.wicket.ajax.AjaxRequestTarget target)
        Pops a series of open drawers from the stack and closes them, displaying the one underneath, or the main page. This method requires an AJAX request. DrawerManager does not support closing drawers during page construction. Note that this code sets each drawer's allow close flag to true. See AbstractDrawer for more information.
        Parameters:
        drawer - The last drawer to be closed. This drawer and all the ones above it are closed. Open drawers beneath this one are not. If this parameter is null or not in the stack, all the drawers are closed.
        target - The current AJAX target. Cannot be null.

      • replaceLast

        public void replaceLast(AbstractDrawer newDrawer,
               org.apache.wicket.ajax.AjaxRequestTarget target)
        Replaces the topmost open drawer with a new one. If there is no open drawer, this method does nothing. This method requires an AJAX request. DrawerManager does not support swapping drawers during page construction.
        Parameters:
        newDrawer - The new drawer to open. Cannot be null.
        target - The current AJAX target. Cannot be null.

      • getLast

        public <T extends AbstractDrawer> T getLast(Class<T> drawerClass)
        Type Parameters:
        T - drawer type
        Parameters:
        drawerClass - The expected class of the topmost open drawer.
        Returns:
